parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose access to critical information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning indicators, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display goes black
speedometer
fuel gauge
and other indicators are not visible
the display flickers or shuts off intermittently
the display is slow to turn on or does not turn on at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the airbag system fails to deploy in a crash
the passenger seat airbag warning light comes on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging station or cord can cause electrical shock, fire, or other safety issues.
symptoms: The charging station overheats
the cord burns or melts
the vehicle does not charge properly
the cord is damaged or exposed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power and propulsion system can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the engine does not shut down
the vehicle will not start
the transmission and engine fault messages appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power, electrical shock, and fire.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system fails
the radio
door locks
and park assist engage/disengage on their own
the brakes do not catch
causing the car to roll.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may prevent the passenger airbag from deploying in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light illuminates
the "Service Airbag" chime and light come on
the passenger airbag will not illuminate or work
the airbag warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Power Steering and Engine
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering and engine can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The power steering fails
the steering wheel becomes hard to maneuver
the engine cuts off without warning
the vehicle loses acceleration
the heat starts blowing cooler air.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear End Instability and Sensitive Steering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear end instability and sensitive steering can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially when entering curves at high speeds.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle feels as if it is slipping out when entering a curve
the vehicle is difficult to control
the steering feels sensitive and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: High Voltage Charging System and Airbag System Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the high voltage charging system and airbag system can cause safety risks, including the failure of critical systems and potential accidents.
symptoms: Warning lights on the dashboard for "Service High Voltage Charging System" and "Service Airbag"
check engine light is on
the vehicle may not charge when plugged in.
